title: PM West picks up its first win of the season
text: PM West picks up its first win of the season Comment Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 10:28 PM Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 10:28 PM Â» Social News PM West 41, Allen 12 Leading rushers: Allen, Muaz Chaudhry 5 carries-93 yards, 1 touchdown; PM West, Matt Mussenden 20 carries-54 yards, 1 touchdown. Leading passes: Allen, Angel Gonzalez 2-2, 44 yards, 1 TD; PM West Dylan Della Valle 17-25 188 2 TDs, INT. Leading receivers: Allen, Christopher Ledee 3-59 yards, 1 TD; PM West, Chris Monaco 9-135 yards 2 TDs. Key play: Pocono West's second play from scrimmage was a 51-yard double pass from Anthony Armstrong to Chris Monaco to start the Panthers' momentum. Key stat: The Panther defense forced six turnovers, two sacks and a safety in PM West's first win of the season. Notes: Chris Monaco, on top of 135 receiving yards and a touchdown reception, had two carries for 22 yards and a rushing touchdown. Next week: Friday, Oct. 16, ES South (2-4) at PM West (1-5), 7 p.m. - Ryan Laroco
